.TH "mtk_infracfg_set_bus_protection" 9 "mtk_infracfg_set_bus_protection" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mtk_infracfg_set_bus_protection \- enable bus protection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mtk_infracfg_set_bus_protection
.BI "(struct regmap *infracfg "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ","
.BI "bool reg_update "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "infracfg" 12
The infracfg regmap
.IP "mask" 12
The mask containing the protection bits to be enabled.
.IP "reg_update" 12
The boolean flag determines to set the protection bits
by regmap_update_bits with enable register(PROTECTEN) or
by regmap_write with set register(PROTECTEN_SET).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function enables the bus protection bits for disabled power
domains so that the system does not hang when some unit accesses the
bus while in power down.
